# Any pytest file should always start with => test_
# pytest method names should start with test_ e.g def test_firstProgram():
# Any code should be wrapped in method only
# keyword to run pytest is: py.test
# Running all pytest from command line: C:\Users\olatu\PycharmProjects1\PythonProject1\PyTest>py.test -v -s
# -k stands for specific  method tag in pytest is return in cmd as -k addition
# -v stands for generating log in pytest
# -s stands for getting more info in pytest
# -m (mark) is used for test tagging like => smoke, regression , e2e in cmd as - m smoke
# @pytest.mark.smoke is used to run smoke test
# @pytest.mark.regression is used to run regression test
# @pytest.mark.skip is used to skip particular test(s) in pytest
# @pytest.mark.xfail is used to skip reporting failed test in particular test(s) in pytest
# @pytest.fixture is used to perform the setup eg browser setup
# yield is used as method for tearDown eg close browser
# conftest is used to warehouse methods, data and browsers that are been used across other test -> like configfile in java
# When you define fixture scope to class only, it will run once before class initiated and after all class method finished.
# To generate html report for executed tests, use: py.test --html=report.html -v -s from the command line, the html report will be created in the test.
# Creating Logs: Debug, info, warning, error, critical, time stamp etc